    "description": "Kansai Nerolac is actively seeking a talented and motivated Manufacturing Engineer to join our dynamic team in Ghaziabad. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Kansai Nerolac:\nKansai Nerolac is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in 5S\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Learning & development budget\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Kansai Nerolac!",
